npc/bayu: You've made it through. Adbots, Bandits, the Witch's collectors — all of them.
npc/bayu: So now you know what online gambling is: real money, pure chance, odds fixed against you — in a dozen disguises, reaching millions.
npc/bayu: But those creatures were just the outer layer. Foot soldiers sent from somewhere deeper.
npc/bayu: Every one of them is projected here through a signal — from inside the internet itself.
npc/bayu: The gate ahead leads into Stage 2: the threshold between this world and the digital one.
npc/bayu: Follow the signal. Trace it back through the network to wherever it begins.
npc/bayu: At the end of it all is something they call the House. The Algorithm. The Core that every other part of this answers to.
npc/bayu: It believes one thing above all else: the house always wins.
npc/bayu: It has never been wrong. Until now.
npc/bayu: Go. And whatever you do — don't play its game.
